Even if this explanation make common sense, it is not in my opinion war- ranted by the genius or usage of the Latin tongue, or even by Livy’s words. Alius in a latter clause of a sentence, implying a part of a whole, has reference to alius expressed or understood in the preceding, and expressing the other part3 and the clauses must be in immediate juxta-position, or evident contrast.
